{"word":"ὑπομιμνήσκω","slug":"ὑπομιμνήσκω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὑπομιμνήσκω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-μνήσω</el>) (aor1 <el>ὑπ-έμνήσα</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a>,<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to remind</i> one <i>of</i> a person or thing, <el>τινά τινος</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; <el>ὑπ. τινά τι</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>: <el>ὑπ. τινά</el> <i>to put</i> him <i>in mind</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to bring back to one's mind, mention, suggest</i>, <el>τι</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>τινί τι</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <i>to remind one of, to make mention of</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> or <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to call to mind, remember</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to make mention</i>, <el>περί τινος</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}